pravartante—begins; vidhāna-uktāḥ—according to scriptural regulation;
satatam—always; brahma-vādinām—of the transcendentalists.  TRANSLATION  Thus the transcendentalists undertake sacrifices, charities, and penances,
beginning always with om, to attain the Supreme.  PURPORT  Om tad viṣṇoḥ paramaṁ padam. The lotus feet of Viṣṇu are the supreme devotional
platform. The performance of everything on behalf of the Supreme Personality of
Godhead assures the perfection of all activity.

tatraivaṁ sati kartāram  ātmānaṁ kevalaṁ tu yaḥ  paśyaty akṛta-buddhitvān  na sa paśyati durmatiḥ  tatra—there; evam—certainly; sati—being thus; kartāram—of the worker;
